<subSubSection pageId="194" pageNumber="797" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="194.[1986,2580,683,1111]" pageId="194" pageNumber="797">
Long considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1837" box="[2428,2580,766,795]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Leggada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="194" pageNumber="797" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="booduga">M. booduga</taxonomicName>
but a recent molecular study by T. Shi- mada and colleagues in 2010 found it to be distinct and very distant from all other species in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[2320,2381,924,953]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Mus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="194" pageNumber="797" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Mus</taxonomicName>
; these authors selected a new holotype, and provided a full morphological description of the spe- cies. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
